69#if PLATFORM(MAC) || PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
70static void wipeAlphaChannelFromPixels(int width, int height, unsigned char* pixels)
71{
72 // We can assume this doesn't overflow because the calling functions
73 // use checked arithmetic.
74 int totalBytes = width * height * 4;
75 for (int i = 0; i < totalBytes; i += 4)
76 pixels[i + 3] = 255;
77}
78#endif

80std::optional<PixelBuffer> GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::readPixelsForPaintResults()
81{
82 PixelBufferFormat format { AlphaPremultiplication::Unpremultiplied, PixelFormat::RGBA8, DestinationColorSpace::SRGB() };
83 auto pixelBuffer = PixelBuffer::tryCreate(format, getInternalFramebufferSize());
84 if (!pixelBuffer)
85 return std::nullopt;
86 ScopedPixelStorageMode packAlignment(GL_PACK_ALIGNMENT);
87 if (packAlignment > 4)
88 packAlignment.pixelStore(4);
89 ScopedPixelStorageMode packRowLength(GL_PACK_ROW_LENGTH, 0, m_isForWebGL2);
90 ScopedPixelStorageMode packSkipRows(GL_PACK_SKIP_ROWS, 0, m_isForWebGL2);
91 ScopedPixelStorageMode packSkipPixels(GL_PACK_SKIP_PIXELS, 0, m_isForWebGL2);
92 ScopedBufferBinding scopedPixelPackBufferReset(GL_PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER, 0, m_isForWebGL2);
93
94 gl::ReadnPixelsRobustANGLE(0, 0, pixelBuffer->size().width(), pixelBuffer->size().height(), GL_RGBA, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, pixelBuffer->data().byteLength(), nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, pixelBuffer->data().data());
95 // FIXME: Rendering to GL_RGB textures with a IOSurface bound to the texture image leaves
96 // the alpha in the IOSurface in incorrect state. Also ANGLE gl::ReadPixels will in some
97 // cases expose the non-255 values.
98 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=215804
99#if PLATFORM(MAC) || PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
100 if (!contextAttributes().alpha)
101 wipeAlphaChannelFromPixels(pixelBuffer->size().width(), pixelBuffer->size().height(), pixelBuffer->data().data());
102#endif
103 return pixelBuffer;
104}

113bool GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::reshapeFBOs(const IntSize& size)
114{
115 auto attrs = contextAttributes();
116 const int width = size.width();
117 const int height = size.height();
118 GLuint colorFormat = attrs.alpha ? GL_RGBA : GL_RGB;
119
120 // Resize multisample FBO.
121 if (attrs.antialias) {
122 GLint maxSampleCount;
123 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_MAX_SAMPLES_ANGLE, &maxSampleCount);
124 // Using more than 4 samples is slow on some hardware and is unlikely to
125 // produce a significantly better result.
126 GLint sampleCount = std::min(4, maxSampleCount);
127 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_multisampleFBO);
128 gl::BindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_multisampleColorBuffer);
129 gl::RenderbufferStorageMultisampleANGLE(GL_RENDERBUFFER, sampleCount, m_internalColorFormat, width, height);
130 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_multisampleColorBuffer);
131 if (attrs.stencil || attrs.depth) {
132 gl::BindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_multisampleDepthStencilBuffer);
133 gl::RenderbufferStorageMultisampleANGLE(GL_RENDERBUFFER, sampleCount, m_internalDepthStencilFormat, width, height);
134 // WebGL 1.0's rules state that combined depth/stencil renderbuffers
135 // have to be attached to the synthetic DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT point.
136 if (!isGLES2Compliant() && m_internalDepthStencilFormat == GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8_OES)
137 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_multisampleDepthStencilBuffer);
138 else {
139 if (attrs.stencil)
140 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_multisampleDepthStencilBuffer);
141 if (attrs.depth)
142 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_multisampleDepthStencilBuffer);
143 }
144 }
145 gl::BindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, 0);
146 if (gl::CheckFramebufferStatus(GL_FRAMEBUFFER) != GL_FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE) {
147 // FIXME: cleanup.
148 notImplemented();
149 }
150 }
151
152 // resize regular FBO
153 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_fbo);
154 ASSERT(m_texture);
155
156#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
157 if (!reshapeDisplayBufferBacking()) {
158 RELEASE_LOG(WebGL, "Fatal: Unable to allocate backing store of size %d x %d", width, height);
159 forceContextLost();
160 return true;
161 }
162 if (m_preserveDrawingBufferTexture) {
163 // The context requires the use of an intermediate texture in order to implement
164 // preserveDrawingBuffer:true without antialiasing.
165 GLint texture2DBinding = 0;
166 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_2D, &texture2DBinding);
167 gl::BindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, m_preserveDrawingBufferTexture);
168 // Note that any pixel unpack buffer was unbound earlier, in reshape().
169 gl::TexImage2D(GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0, colorFormat, width, height, 0, colorFormat, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, 0);
170 // m_fbo is bound at this point.
171 gl::FramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, GL_TEXTURE_2D, m_preserveDrawingBufferTexture, 0);
172 gl::BindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, texture2DBinding);
173 // Attach m_texture to m_preserveDrawingBufferFBO for later blitting.
174 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_preserveDrawingBufferFBO);
175 gl::FramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, drawingBufferTextureTarget(), m_texture, 0);
176 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_fbo);
177 } else
178 gl::FramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, drawingBufferTextureTarget(), m_texture, 0);
179#else
180 GLenum textureTarget = drawingBufferTextureTarget();
181 GLuint internalColorFormat = textureTarget == GL_TEXTURE_2D ? colorFormat : m_internalColorFormat;
182 gl::BindTexture(textureTarget, m_texture);
183 gl::TexImage2D(textureTarget, 0, internalColorFormat, width, height, 0, colorFormat, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, 0);
184 gl::FramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, textureTarget, m_texture, 0);
185#if USE(COORDINATED_GRAPHICS)
186 if (m_compositorTexture) {
187 gl::BindTexture(textureTarget, m_compositorTexture);
188 gl::TexImage2D(textureTarget, 0, m_internalColorFormat, width, height, 0, colorFormat, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, 0);
189 gl::BindTexture(textureTarget, 0);
190 gl::BindTexture(textureTarget, m_intermediateTexture);
191 gl::TexImage2D(textureTarget, 0, m_internalColorFormat, width, height, 0, colorFormat, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, 0);
192 gl::BindTexture(textureTarget, 0);
193 }
194#endif
195#endif // PLATFORM(COCOA)
196
197 attachDepthAndStencilBufferIfNeeded(m_internalDepthStencilFormat, width, height);
198
199 bool mustRestoreFBO = true;
200 if (attrs.antialias) {
201 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_multisampleFBO);
202 if (m_state.boundDrawFBO == m_multisampleFBO && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_multisampleFBO)
203 mustRestoreFBO = false;
204 } else {
205 if (m_state.boundDrawFBO == m_fbo && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_fbo)
206 mustRestoreFBO = false;
207 }
208
209 return mustRestoreFBO;
210}
211
212void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::attachDepthAndStencilBufferIfNeeded(GLuint internalDepthStencilFormat, int width, int height)
213{
214 auto attrs = contextAttributes();
215
216 if (!attrs.antialias && (attrs.stencil || attrs.depth)) {
217 gl::BindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_depthStencilBuffer);
218 gl::RenderbufferStorage(GL_RENDERBUFFER, internalDepthStencilFormat, width, height);
219 // WebGL 1.0's rules state that combined depth/stencil renderbuffers
220 // have to be attached to the synthetic DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT point.
221 if (!isGLES2Compliant() && internalDepthStencilFormat == GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8_OES)
222 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_depthStencilBuffer);
223 else {
224 if (attrs.stencil)
225 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_depthStencilBuffer);
226 if (attrs.depth)
227 gl::FramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER, m_depthStencilBuffer);
228 }
229 gl::BindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, 0);
230 }
231
232 if (gl::CheckFramebufferStatus(GL_FRAMEBUFFER) != GL_FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE) {
233 // FIXME: cleanup
234 notImplemented();
235 }
236}

238void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::resolveMultisamplingIfNecessary(const IntRect& rect)
239{
240 TemporaryANGLESetting scopedScissor(GL_SCISSOR_TEST, GL_FALSE);
241 TemporaryANGLESetting scopedDither(GL_DITHER, GL_FALSE);
242
243 GLint boundFrameBuffer = 0;
244 GLint boundReadFrameBuffer = 0;
245 if (m_isForWebGL2) {
246 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING, &boundFrameBuffer);
247 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING, &boundReadFrameBuffer);
248 } else
249 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING, &boundFrameBuffer);
250 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_ANGLE, m_multisampleFBO);
251 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_ANGLE, m_fbo);
252
253 // FIXME: figure out more efficient solution for iOS.
254 if (m_isForWebGL2) {
255 // ES 3.0 has BlitFramebuffer.
256 IntRect resolveRect = rect.isEmpty() ? IntRect { 0, 0, m_currentWidth, m_currentHeight } : rect;
257 gl::BlitFramebuffer(resolveRect.x(), resolveRect.y(), resolveRect.maxX(), resolveRect.maxY(), resolveRect.x(), resolveRect.y(), resolveRect.maxX(), resolveRect.maxY(), GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT, GL_NEAREST);
258 } else {
259 // ES 2.0 has BlitFramebufferANGLE only.
260 gl::BlitFramebufferANGLE(0, 0, m_currentWidth, m_currentHeight, 0, 0, m_currentWidth, m_currentHeight, GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT, GL_NEAREST);
261 }
262 if (m_isForWebGL2) {
263 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, boundFrameBuffer);
264 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER, boundReadFrameBuffer);
265 } else
266 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, boundFrameBuffer);
267}

382
383void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::readnPixelsImpl(GCGLint x, GCGLint y, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLsizei bufSize, GCGLsizei* length, GCGLsizei* columns, GCGLsizei* rows, GCGLvoid* data, bool readingToPixelBufferObject)
384{
385 if (!makeContextCurrent())
386 return;
387
388 // FIXME: remove the two glFlush calls when the driver bug is fixed, i.e.,
389 // all previous rendering calls should be done before reading pixels.
390 gl::Flush();
391 auto attrs = contextAttributes();
392 GCGLenum framebufferTarget = m_isForWebGL2 ? GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER : GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER;
393 if (attrs.antialias && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_multisampleFBO) {
394 resolveMultisamplingIfNecessary(IntRect(x, y, width, height));
395 gl::BindFramebuffer(framebufferTarget, m_fbo);
396 gl::Flush();
397 }
398 moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
399 gl::ReadnPixelsRobustANGLE(x, y, width, height, format, type, bufSize, length, columns, rows, data);
400 GLenum error = gl::GetError();
401 if (attrs.antialias && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_multisampleFBO)
402 gl::BindFramebuffer(framebufferTarget, m_multisampleFBO);
403
404 if (error) {
405 // ANGLE detected a failure during the ReadnPixelsRobustANGLE operation. Surface this in the
406 // synthetic error list, and skip the alpha channel fixup below.
407 synthesizeGLError(error);
408 return;
409 }
410
411
412#if PLATFORM(MAC) || PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
413 if (!readingToPixelBufferObject && !attrs.alpha && (format == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA || format == GraphicsContextGL::BGRA) && (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE) && (m_state.boundReadFBO == m_fbo || (attrs.antialias && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_multisampleFBO)))
414 wipeAlphaChannelFromPixels(width, height, static_cast<unsigned char*>(data));
415#else
416 UNUSED_PARAM(readingToPixelBufferObject);
417#endif
418}

420// The contents of GraphicsContextGLOpenGLCommon follow, ported to use ANGLE.
421
422void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::validateDepthStencil(const char* packedDepthStencilExtension)
423{
424 ExtensionsGL& extensions = getExtensions();
425 // FIXME: Since the constructors of various platforms are not shared, we initialize this here.
426 // Upon constructing the context, always initialize the extensions that the WebGLRenderingContext* will
427 // use to turn on feature flags.
428 if (extensions.supports(packedDepthStencilExtension)) {
429 extensions.ensureEnabled(packedDepthStencilExtension);
430 m_internalDepthStencilFormat = GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8_OES;
431 } else
432 m_internalDepthStencilFormat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT16;
433
434 auto attrs = contextAttributes();
435 if (attrs.stencil) {
436 if (m_internalDepthStencilFormat == GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8_OES) {
437 // Force depth if stencil is true.
438 attrs.depth = true;
439 } else
440 attrs.stencil = false;
441 setContextAttributes(attrs);
442 }
443
444 if (attrs.antialias) {
445 // FIXME: must adjust this when upgrading to WebGL 2.0 / OpenGL ES 3.0 support.
446 if (!extensions.supports("GL_ANGLE_framebuffer_multisample") || !extensions.supports("GL_ANGLE_framebuffer_blit") || !extensions.supports("GL_OES_rgb8_rgba8")) {
447 attrs.antialias = false;
448 setContextAttributes(attrs);
449 } else {
450 extensions.ensureEnabled("GL_ANGLE_framebuffer_multisample");
451 extensions.ensureEnabled("GL_ANGLE_framebuffer_blit");
452 extensions.ensureEnabled("GL_OES_rgb8_rgba8");
453 }
454 } else if (attrs.preserveDrawingBuffer) {
455 // Needed for preserveDrawingBuffer:true support without antialiasing.
456 extensions.ensureEnabled("GL_ANGLE_framebuffer_blit");
457 }
458}

460void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::prepareTexture()
461{
462 if (m_layerComposited)
463 return;
464
465 if (!makeContextCurrent())
466 return;
467
468 prepareTextureImpl();
469}
470
471void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::prepareTextureImpl()
472{
473 ASSERT(!m_layerComposited);
474
475 if (contextAttributes().antialias)
476 resolveMultisamplingIfNecessary();
477
478#if USE(COORDINATED_GRAPHICS)
479 std::swap(m_texture, m_compositorTexture);
480 std::swap(m_texture, m_intermediateTexture);
481 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_fbo);
482 gl::FramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE_ANGLE, m_texture, 0);
483 gl::Flush();
484
485 if (m_state.boundDrawFBO != m_fbo)
486 gl::BindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, m_state.boundDrawFBO);
487 else
488 gl::BindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, m_fbo);
489#else
490 if (m_preserveDrawingBufferTexture) {
491 // Blit m_preserveDrawingBufferTexture into m_texture.
492 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_ANGLE, m_preserveDrawingBufferFBO);
493 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_ANGLE, m_fbo);
494 gl::BlitFramebufferANGLE(0, 0, m_currentWidth, m_currentHeight, 0, 0, m_currentWidth, m_currentHeight, GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT, GL_NEAREST);
495
496 // Note: it's been observed that BlitFramebuffer may destroy the alpha channel of the
497 // destination texture if it's an RGB texture bound to an IOSurface. This wasn't observable
498 // through the WebGL conformance tests, but it may be necessary to save and restore the
499 // color mask and clear color, and use the color mask to clear the alpha channel of the
500 // destination texture to 1.0.
501
502 // Restore user's framebuffer bindings.
503 if (m_isForWebGL2) {
504 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, m_state.boundDrawFBO);
505 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER, m_state.boundReadFBO);
506 } else
507 gl::BindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, m_state.boundDrawFBO);
508 }
509#endif
510}
511
512std::optional<PixelBuffer> GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::readRenderingResults()
513{
514 ScopedRestoreReadFramebufferBinding fboBinding(m_isForWebGL2, m_state.boundReadFBO);
515 if (contextAttributes().antialias) {
516 resolveMultisamplingIfNecessary();
517 fboBinding.markBindingChanged();
518 }
519 fboBinding.bindFramebuffer(m_fbo);
520 return readPixelsForPaintResults();
521}
522
523void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::reshape(int width, int height)
524{
525 if (width == m_currentWidth && height == m_currentHeight)
526 return;
527
528 ASSERT(width >= 0 && height >= 0);
529 if (width < 0 || height < 0)
530 return;
531
532 if (!makeContextCurrent())
533 return;
534
535 // FIXME: these may call makeContextCurrent again, we need to do this before changing the size.
536 moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
537 validateAttributes();
538
539 markContextChanged();
540
541 m_currentWidth = width;
542 m_currentHeight = height;
543
544 TemporaryANGLESetting scopedScissor(GL_SCISSOR_TEST, GL_FALSE);
545 TemporaryANGLESetting scopedDither(GL_DITHER, GL_FALSE);
546 ScopedBufferBinding scopedPixelUnpackBufferReset(GL_PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER, 0, m_isForWebGL2);
547
548 bool mustRestoreFBO = reshapeFBOs(IntSize(width, height));
549 auto attrs = contextAttributes();
550
551 // Initialize renderbuffers to 0.
552 GLfloat clearColor[] = {0, 0, 0, 0}, clearDepth = 0;
553 GLint clearStencil = 0;
554 GLboolean colorMask[] = {GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE}, depthMask = GL_TRUE;
555 GLuint stencilMask = 0xffffffff, stencilMaskBack = 0xffffffff;
556 GLbitfield clearMask = GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT;
557 gl::GetFloatv(GL_COLOR_CLEAR_VALUE, clearColor);
558 gl::ClearColor(0, 0, 0, 0);
559 gl::GetBooleanv(GL_COLOR_WRITEMASK, colorMask);
560 gl::ColorMask(GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE);
561 if (attrs.depth) {
562 gl::GetFloatv(GL_DEPTH_CLEAR_VALUE, &clearDepth);
563 gl::ClearDepthf(1.0f);
564 gl::GetBooleanv(GL_DEPTH_WRITEMASK, &depthMask);
565 gl::DepthMask(GL_TRUE);
566 clearMask |= GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT;
567 }
568
569 if (attrs.stencil) {
570 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_STENCIL_CLEAR_VALUE, &clearStencil);
571 gl::ClearStencil(0);
572 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_STENCIL_WRITEMASK, reinterpret_cast<GLint*>(&stencilMask));
573 gl::GetIntegerv(GL_STENCIL_BACK_WRITEMASK, reinterpret_cast<GLint*>(&stencilMaskBack));
574 gl::StencilMaskSeparate(GL_FRONT, 0xffffffff);
575 gl::StencilMaskSeparate(GL_BACK, 0xffffffff);
576 clearMask |= GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
577 }
578
579 gl::Clear(clearMask);
580
581 gl::ClearColor(clearColor[0], clearColor[1], clearColor[2], clearColor[3]);
582 gl::ColorMask(colorMask[0], colorMask[1], colorMask[2], colorMask[3]);
583 if (attrs.depth) {
584 gl::ClearDepthf(clearDepth);
585 gl::DepthMask(depthMask);
586 }
587 if (attrs.stencil) {
588 gl::ClearStencil(clearStencil);
589 gl::StencilMaskSeparate(GL_FRONT, stencilMask);
590 gl::StencilMaskSeparate(GL_BACK, stencilMaskBack);
591 }
592
593 if (mustRestoreFBO) {
594 gl::BindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, m_state.boundDrawFBO);
595 if (m_isForWebGL2 && m_state.boundDrawFBO != m_state.boundReadFBO)
596 gl::BindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER, m_state.boundReadFBO);
597 }
598
599 auto error = gl::GetError();
600 if (error != GL_NO_ERROR) {
601 RELEASE_LOG(WebGL, "Fatal: OpenGL error during GraphicsContextGL buffer initialization (%d).", error);
602 forceContextLost();
603 return;
604 }
605
606 gl::Flush();
607}

645void GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::bindFramebuffer(GCGLenum target, PlatformGLObject buffer)
646{
647 if (!makeContextCurrent())
648 return;
649
650 GLuint fbo;
651 if (buffer)
652 fbo = buffer;
653 else
654 fbo = (contextAttributes().antialias ? m_multisampleFBO : m_fbo);
655
656 gl::BindFramebuffer(target, fbo);
657 if (target == GL_FRAMEBUFFER) {
658 m_state.boundReadFBO = m_state.boundDrawFBO = fbo;
659 } else if (target == GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER) {
660 m_state.boundReadFBO = fbo;
661 } else if (target == GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER) {
662 m_state.boundDrawFBO = fbo;
663 }
664}

934{

936 return;
937
938 auto attrs = contextAttributes();

940
941 if (attrs.antialias && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_multisampleFBO) {
942 resolveMultisamplingIfNecessary(IntRect(x, y, width, height));

946 if (attrs.antialias && m_state.boundReadFBO == m_multisampleFBO)
947 gl::BindFramebuffer(framebufferTarget, m_multisampleFBO);
948}

1100bool GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::getActiveAttribImpl(PlatformGLObject program, GCGLuint index, ActiveInfo& info)
1101{
1102 if (!program) {
1103 synthesizeGLError(INVALID_VALUE);
1104 return false;
1105 }
1106 if (!makeContextCurrent())
1107 return false;
1108
1109 GLint maxAttributeSize = 0;
1110 gl::GetProgramiv(program, GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTE_MAX_LENGTH, &maxAttributeSize);
1111 Vector<GLchar> name(maxAttributeSize); // GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTE_MAX_LENGTH includes null termination.
1112 GLsizei nameLength = 0;
1113 GLint size = 0;
1114 GLenum type = 0;
1115 gl::GetActiveAttrib(program, index, maxAttributeSize, &nameLength, &size, &type, name.data());
1116 if (!nameLength)
1117 return false;
1118
1119 info.name = String(name.data(), nameLength);
1120 info.type = type;
1121 info.size = size;
1122 return true;
1123}
1124
1125bool GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::getActiveAttrib(PlatformGLObject program, GCGLuint index, ActiveInfo& info)
1126{
1127 return getActiveAttribImpl(program, index, info);
1128}

1189
1190bool GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()
1191{
1192 if (!makeContextCurrent())
1193 return false;
1194
1195 bool movedAnError = false;
1196
1197 // Set an arbitrary limit of 100 here to avoid creating a hang if
1198 // a problem driver has a bug that causes it to never clear the error.
1199 // Otherwise, we would just loop until we got NO_ERROR.
1200 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
1201 GCGLenum error = gl::GetError();
1202 if (error == NO_ERROR)
1203 break;
1204 m_syntheticErrors.add(error);
1205 movedAnError = true;
1206 }
1207
1208 return movedAnError;
1209}
1210
1211GCGLenum GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::getError()
1212{
1213 if (!m_syntheticErrors.isEmpty()) {
1214 // Need to move the current errors to the synthetic error list in case
1215 // that error is already there, since the expected behavior of both
1216 // glGetError and getError is to only report each error code once.
1217 moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
1218 return m_syntheticErrors.takeFirst();
1219 }
1220
1221 if (!makeContextCurrent())
1222 return GL_INVALID_OPERATION;
1223
1224 return gl::GetError();
1225}

1818
1819String GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::getUnmangledInfoLog(PlatformGLObject shaders[2], GCGLsizei count, const String& log)
1820{
1821 UNUSED_PARAM(shaders);
1822 UNUSED_PARAM(count);
1823 LOG(WebGL, "Original ShaderInfoLog:\n%s", log.utf8().data());
1824
1825 StringBuilder processedLog;
1826
1827 // ANGLE inserts a "#extension" line into the shader source that
1828 // causes a warning in some compilers. There is no point showing
1829 // this warning to the user since they didn't write the code that
1830 // is causing it.
1831 static const NeverDestroyed<String> angleWarning { "WARNING: 0:1: extension 'GL_ARB_gpu_shader5' is not supported\n"_s };
1832 int startFrom = log.startsWith(angleWarning) ? angleWarning.get().length() : 0;
1833 processedLog.append(log.substring(startFrom, log.length() - startFrom));
1834
1835 LOG(WebGL, "Unmangled ShaderInfoLog:\n%s", processedLog.toString().utf8().data());
1836 return processedLog.toString();
1837}
1838
1839String GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::getProgramInfoLog(PlatformGLObject program)
1840{
1841 ASSERT(program);
1842
1843 if (!makeContextCurrent())
1844 return String();
1845
1846 GLint length = 0;
1847 gl::GetProgramiv(program, GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH, &length);
1848 if (!length)
1849 return String();
1850
1851 GLsizei size = 0;
1852 Vector<GLchar> info(length);
1853 gl::GetProgramInfoLog(program, length, &size, info.data());
1854
1855 GCGLsizei count;
1856 PlatformGLObject shaders[2];
1857 getAttachedShaders(program, 2, &count, shaders);
1858
1859 return getUnmangledInfoLog(shaders, count, String(info.data(), size));
1860}

2037{

2042 // operations after it gets deleted.

2045 bindFramebuffer(DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, 0);

2051}
